  <title>MD-Function-Block-Point-Data-Measurement</title>
  <keywords>
    <keyword>kinematic-data</keyword>
    <keyword>Measurement FB</keyword>
    <keyword>Point-Data FB</keyword>
  </keywords>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Point-Data FB:</text> they can measure the <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Motion">motion-values</link> of any Point in the model. The Point might be a start-Point, End-Point, center-Point or Motion-Point along a sketch-path.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box-Elements">Measurement FB:</text> can measure the motion-values between Points and Lines.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The motion-values at the output-connectors can be plotted with a Graph FB or used as independent variable at the input to a different FB.</para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">See also: <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-Point-Data" styleclass="T_Menusmall">Add Point-Data FB</link><text styleclass="T_Menusmall">, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-Measurement" styleclass="T_Menusmall">Measurement FB</link><text styleclass="T_Menusmall">, </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-FB-Motion" styleclass="T_Menusmall">Motion FB</link></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
